## Content Tailoring by Audience

The same underlying analysis gets presented differently depending on entry point:

| Content Element | HN Presentation | Teacher Presentation | Academic Presentation |
|---|---|---|---|
| Differential diagnosis | Full analysis with scoring tables | Simplified "competing explanations" activity | Full analysis + methodology appendix |
| Evidence matrix | Interactive sortable table | Worksheet with guided evaluation | Downloadable CSV + replication notes |
| ICESCR articles | Linked organically from analysis | Lesson plans per article | Cross-referenced with legal commentary |
| Higher-order effects | Full cascade visualization | "What happens next?" classroom discussion | Formal chain analysis with confidence intervals |
| Causal chains | ASCII diagrams (they love these) | Simplified flowcharts for classroom | Formal DAG notation option |
| Action items | Template letters, senator lookup | Lesson plan on civic participation | Policy brief format |
| Tagline visible | "Human Rights Observatory, Hacker News Edition" | "Classroom Resources for Human Rights Education" | "Research and Methodology" |

---

## Launch Sequencing by Audience

```
PHASE в”Ӯ AUDIENCE   в”Ӯ ACTION                                в”Ӯ GOAL
в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
  1   в”Ӯ HN         в”Ӯ Submit observatory analysis to HN     в”Ӯ Attention +
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ Title: analysis-focused, not advocacy  в”Ӯ credibility
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ                                        в”Ӯ
  2   в”Ӯ Academic   в”Ӯ Post methodology to SSRN / arXiv      в”Ӯ Citation +
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ Announce on academic social media      в”Ӯ validation
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ                                        в”Ӯ
  3   в”Ӯ Teacher    в”Ӯ Educator outreach via networks,        в”Ӯ Adoption +
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ conferences, NEA/AFT channels          в”Ӯ durability
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ                                        в”Ӯ
  вҲһ   в”Ӯ All        в”Ӯ Quarterly updates as landscape evolves в”Ӯ Sustained
      в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ Annual differential diagnosis refresh  в”Ӯ relevance
```

**Rationale for sequencing**: HN provides the initial amplification burst. Academic engagement provides credibility that supports the educator pitch. Educator adoption creates the most durable long-term impact (shapes the judgment pipeline вҖ” the Article 13 argument in action).

